Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community,
Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 3760/92 of 20 December 1992 establishing a Community system for fisheries and aquaculture (1), and in particular Article 8 (4) thereof,
Having regard to the proposal from the Commission,
Whereas under the terms of Article 8 (4) of Regulation (EEC) No 3760/92 it is incumbent upon the Council to establish the total allowable catches (TACs) by fishery or group of fisheries;
Whereas Regulation (EC) No 3074/95 (2) fixes, for certain fish stocks and groups of fish stocks, the TACs for 1996 and certain conditions under which they may be fished;
Whereas, due to the positive evolution of the stock of sprat in the Skagerrak and the Kattegat, a profitable use of the fishing possibilities allocated to the European Union for 1996 requires fishing this stock with nets with a maximum mesh size of 16 mm;
Whereas a review of the management system for North Sea herring is foreseen in 1996 for adoption in 1997;
Whereas it would be uneconomical for Community fishermen to purchase in the interim period nets of mesh sizes other than those which they are currently authorized to use;
Whereas Regulation (EC) No 3074/95 should be amended accordingly,
